class_name CardTierCatalog
## Complexity tier for every Pokémon card's attack/ability effects.
##
## Tiers:
##   0 — Pure base damage; no effect text; no EffectRegistry handler needed.
##       The existing ActionAttack system handles these completely.
##
##   1 — One simple, self-contained effect:
##         · Coin flip gating bonus damage or a status condition
##         · Unconditional status condition (Asleep, Paralyzed, Poisoned, …)
##         · Optional self-energy discard for a bonus
##         · Simple "N × own energy" or "N × damage counters on target" scaling
##         · Prevent-retreat lock
##         · Small self-heal / remove damage counters
##         · Attach energy from discard to self
##
##   2 — Moderate complexity:
##         · Bench damage (opponent's bench, own bench, all bench)
##         · Deck or discard search
##         · Draw effects
##         · Damage prevention / reduction for a full turn
##         · Energy movement between Pokémon
##         · Forced switch / retreat
##         · Damage scaling across all Pokémon's energy counts
##
##   3 — Complex multi-step or context-sensitive effects:
##         · Opponent hand inspection or disruption
##         · Prize-count conditionals
##         · Multi-turn persistent modifiers
##         · Damage scaling vs. opponent's resource counts
##         · Multi-attack combo chains or unique card-specific rules
##
## Non-Pokémon cards (Trainers, Energy) are not listed here.
## Note: Tiers 1–3 are working approximations; they will be refined as each
## card's EffectRegistry handler is written and tested.

